The swing-by is a flight manoeuvre by spacecraft, in which they receive additional momentum in the gravitational field of a celestial body, such as the Earth.
This allows the probes to save a lot of fuel.
The European-American spacecraft Cassini-Huygens used this physical trick as well as the solar probe Ulysses.
