Heinz-Christian Strache, a leftist of the Austrian right-wing Freedom Party of Austria, and Filip Dewinter, a member of the Belgian right-wing Pertei Vlaams Belang, will participate in a demonstration in Antwerp on Thursday, January 17, 2008 to represent the organization "Cities against Islamization".
They wear signs in the style of traffic signs on which a mosque is depicted, painted with a red line.
Police accuse far-right extremists of corrupting a Muslim cemetery in Austria on the same weekend that far-right parties recorded significant gains in the country’s parliamentary elections.
