He must notify the authorities if he intends to travel abroad for more than three days.
He must also notify the police 7 days before his planned departure.
Failure to notify the authorities could result in a prison sentence of 5 years.
Kent police said they would not discuss individual cases or Glitter’s possible location in the country.
A spokeswoman for Kent’s police unit said: “The Kent police will do everything necessary to protect children in this country and abroad.”
“In our view, it is easier to control someone who is in the UK because we have a comprehensive system to effectively prevent any potential risks.”
“It is Kent police’s primary concern to protect the residents of Kent and we are working closely together to monitor the behavior of registered sexual offenders in the country to minimize any risk that could exist for the population.
Glitter returned to the UK last month after spending 27 months in a Vietnamese prison for abusing 2 girls aged 10 and 11.
