Finally, he arrived at Terminal 3 in Heathrow on August 22 and stayed there while his lawyer David Corker went to the Uxbridge District Court in West London after Scotland Yard had successfully sought permission to request that he be registered as a sexual offender.
Glitter had previously been imprisoned in 1999 for 4 months in the UK for possession of images of child abuse.
Interior Minister Jacqui Smith said she was reassured and pleased that Glitter was prevented from traveling to France and Spain.
