In his project `Flamenco-people' the German photographer Günter Bauer depicts a varied Theatralik of some stage performances with singers, dancers and guitarists.
With this proposal, the photographer creates a special iconography of the flamenco display at different levels.
The exhibition, which is part of the programme of the Month of Flamenco Photography, “reflects the international importance of Flamenco, which is growing from day to day,” the artist explains and makes it clear that “Flamenco people” “can be anyone, but when you look at the photos, the viewer notices that there are no typical images of artists on stage.
