In order to capture the personality of these artists, you do not need to take pictures on stage.
Their personality and character are in their hearts.
What I was interested in was creating a personal atmosphere that would allow me to capture the characters of the greatest flamenco comedians with the camera.”
Inspired by the Cante de las Minas festival, Bauer embarked on a long journey in 1997 to photograph singers, guitarists or dancers with a digital camera.
Thanks to the image sorting function of the camera and the existing material, images that resemble classical photography were created.
