The witness told in detail that Locklear “pressed the gas pedal after 4:30 p.m. and made a lot of noise trying to move her car back or forward from the parking lot, and as she drove back, she grabbed her sunglasses a few times.”
A little later, the witness, who initially probably hadn’t noticed the actress, saw Locklear stopping on a nearby road and coming out of the car.
The witness was the person who notified the emergency service because she was 'fearful for Locklears life'.
When the police arrived, they found the actress sitting in her car, which stood across the street, thus blocking traffic.
‘She seemed to be unoriented,’ so they took the police to a special drug and alcohol center to do a test.
According to a police spokesman, the actress showed cooperative, excessive alcohol consumption was excluded from the first moment. `Following the initial observations of officials, we believe that Locklear was under the influence of an unknown drug,' the spokesman said.
Locklear was arrested on suspicion of driving under the influence of an undetermined substance, which could not be determined, and placed in a local investigative detention center around 7 p.m.
Two months ago, Locklaer was fired from a clinic in Arizona, where she was treated for anxiety and depression.
